The paper discusses distributed machine learning, specifically stochastic gradient descent, in the context of big data. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also addresses the issue of Byzantine attacks, which falls under the scope of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper involves the use of smart devices and sensors, which could be classified under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also deals with the collection and analysis of large volumes of data, which could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper proposes machine learning algorithms, which could be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
